input.command:
gh issue create --repo surrealdb/surrealdb \
  --title "Bug: search::score() and @N@ match operator fail inside DEFINE FUNCTION" \
  --body "$(cat <<'EOF'
## Describe the bug

`search::score(N)` and the `@N@` match operator do not work inside `DEFINE FUNCTION`. When a query using `@1@` and `search::score(1)` is executed directly, it works correctly. When the same query is placed inside a stored function, it fails with:

```
Invalid query: Index function 'search::score': no MATCHES clause found in WHERE condition
```

The BM25 predicate reference is lost across the `DEFINE FUNCTION` boundary.

## Steps to reproduce

```sql
-- Setup
DEFINE ANALYZER test_analyzer TOKENIZERS blank, class, camel, punct FILTERS snowball(english), lowercase;
DEFINE TABLE test SCHEMAFULL;
DEFINE FIELD text ON test TYPE string;
DEFINE INDEX idx_test_fulltext ON test FIELDS text FULLTEXT ANALYZER test_analyzer BM25(1.2, 0.75);

CREATE test SET text = "IAM vision: Agents have identity and authority scopes";
CREATE test SET text = "Governance model: Feed is the single governance surface";
CREATE test SET text = "Target market is solo founders and tiny teams";

-- Direct query: WORKS ✓
SELECT id, text, search::score(1) AS score
FROM test
WHERE text @1@ "governance"
ORDER BY score DESC;
-- Returns: score=1.815, "Governance model: ..."

-- Inside stored function: FAILS ✗
DEFINE FUNCTION fn::test_search($query: string) {
  LET $rows = SELECT id, text, search::score(1) AS score
  FROM test
  WHERE text @1@ $query
  ORDER BY score DESC LIMIT 5;
  RETURN $rows;
};

RETURN fn::test_search("governance");
-- Error: Invalid query: Index function 'search::score': no MATCHES clause found in WHERE condition
```

## Expected behaviour

The `@N@` match operator and `search::score(N)` should work identically inside `DEFINE FUNCTION` as they do in direct queries.

## SurrealDB version

`surreal-2.6.1` for macOS on aarch64

## Contact Details

_No response_

## Is there an existing issue for this?

- [x] I have searched the existing issues
EOF
)"

